Earlier in the year, Future released The Wizrd which gave the Atlanta rapper his fifth straight No. 1 on the Billboard 200 albums chart. With The Wizrd, Future overtook Drake for the most No. 1s on the Top R&B/Hip-Hop Albums chart for the entire decade, with nine leaders. The prolific rapper is back for more. After a brief, and ambiguous, teaser campaign, Future has dropped his new EP, Save Me. Spanning seven tracks, Save Me dropped on Friday, June 6 and can be streamed in full below:  